title: Grant Wood American Gothic Mug
description:
Mug developed from Grant Wood’s American Gothic, 1930, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

American Gothic, 1932, was exhibited publicly for the first time at the Art Institute of Chicago, winning him a $300 prize and instant fame.  Our ceramic mug features a detail of this painting.

  • Size: 11oz.
  • Dimensions: 3.26 x 3.75 in.
  • Material: Ceramic
  • Dishwasher (top rack) and microwave safe.
